00033 /// structure to hold OBD service commands
00034 struct obdservicecmd {
00035     unsigned int cmdid; ///< Command ID [eg 0C == engine rpm]
00036     int bytes_returned; ///< Number of bytes we expect back for this item. Elm327 optimisation [0 == no optimisation]
00037     const char *db_column; ///< Database column name.
00038     const char *human_name; ///< Human friendly name. http://www.kbmsystems.net/obd_tech.htm
00039     float min_value; ///< Minimum allowable value [after conversion]
00040     float max_value; ///< Maximum allowable value [after conversion]
00041     const char *units; ///< Human friendly representation of units
00042     OBDConvFunc conv; ///< Function to convert OBD values for this command to a useful number
00043     OBDConvRevFunc convrev; ///< Function to convert a useful number back to OBD values
00044 };
00045 
00046 /// Return the obdservicecmd struct for the requested db_column name
00047 /** This function is O(n) including a strcmp. You probably don't
00048 want to call it very often. */
00049 struct obdservicecmd *obdGetCmdForColumn(const char *db_column);
00050 
00051 /// Return the obdservicecmd struct for the requested db_column name
00052 /** This function is O(n). You probably don't
00053 want to call it very often. */
00054 struct obdservicecmd *obdGetCmdForPID(const unsigned int pid);
